should i have a baby shower this is my st baby my best friend is dying to throw me a shower however i hesitate to let her for a variety of reasons i just got married in feb had a bridal shower in january i feel that a shower would just be another event focused on me that costs my friends money i'm not a foo foo baby shower type of person i feel that the large group would be overwhelming there is just no way i could have a small shower there are too many people in our life my hubby's stepmom mom don't get along this could be stressful for me even if they are well behaved together we are fortunate enough to not need a baby registry soooooo all that being said you'd think i wouldn't want one at all but there's another side of me that feels like i might regret not having one should i just let my friend take the reigns and throw one for me or is there something else we can do please help thank you in advance go with your gut feeling i can understand your reasons for not wanting one i'm not the party for me type but i loved my baby shower for me it wasn't even the shower it's self it was after the fact going through all the things that i got but that was a long time ago and the baby registry wasn't popular then i enjoyed getting things from experienced mothers that i would have never thought of getting if you really have a bad feeling about it then don't have one but if you do i bet you won't regret it Phoebe Buffay's songs Humphrey Bogart Charmed Theory of conduct Infantilism Knots Landing EastEnders Jon Secada Avenue Q The Apprentice 2 Cliff Richard The Catcher in the Rye Poker jargon Craps Nicomachean Ethics Eddie Guerrero Sydney Riot of 1879 One Tree Hill (TV series) Night (book) Social rule Kimi Finster Satchel Paige Shaggy dog story Rugrats Slow Train Coming Sauna Mina Mongoose Transactional analysis Characters in the Smurfs Glen Jacobs Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Eric Cartman Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Urinary incontinence Scrooge McDuc